messages.content:
Exiting the bakery and leaning against the outside wall, he let out a shaky sigh.
Helio... the guy terrified him more than anything he can think of, but he doesn't know why.

"Polaris...?"
Malachite steps outside, looking at him with concern.
"What's wrong?"

He turned his head to Malachite, for some reason not thinking the other would come outside with him.
"Just... got a bad feeling."

"Mhm..."
He sets a hand on his arm and looks up at him.
"Do we need to leave?"

A sigh.
"No.. I don't want to leave so suddenly, 'specially on Solus' birthday.. I. I need to talk to someone after, though. One on one."
"...Alright."
"You sure you're okay? Do you need to be alone? I can go inside, if you want."
He nodded hesitantly. "Yeah.. Thanks."

"Alright. Okay."
He glances back up, giving Polaris a reassuring pat before hesitantly walking away.

After a moment, he lets out another sigh.
...He's not looking forward to this talk.
Gemi is crying
*you owe everyone an apology.*
Her cracks started to glow ... and worsen
She just sat and cried
“Gemini?!”
Wanderer looks upset. *Why is she crying...?*
Solus walks out. "Gemi! Where are you? We care about you!"
"Just ... Go back inside and enjoy your birthday. I'm sorry I made a scene..."
He sits down next to her. "Gemi, you don't have to apologize."
"Just go back inside-"
Reminder that Splat is still just sitting there chilling.
He goes back in for a moment.
“What’s the matter?” Parcival asks.
"You all go inside. Don't mind me."
Shale walks up behind her. "Hey." She waves everyone back inside. *I'll deal with this.*
Star vanishes.
"Shale, go back inside."
"Gemi." Shale walks round into Gemi's field of vision. *That makes people more comfortable.*
"Don't worry. Just enjoy the party with everyone else. I'm sorry I made a scene."
"Gemi, stop that." Shale kneels beside her.
*Gemi, stop being a fucking burden on everyone* "I'm sorry I made you worry..."

"I'm not.... worried, per say. I think you're a strong, capable woman, who can do anything if she puts her mind to it. I think you're an amazing person and a wonderful friend. But most of all." Shale turns Gemi's face to her. "You're my girlfriend, and I care about you. I care about you more than anything else. And when I see that my girlfriend needs help, I'm going to help her. It doesn't diminish my respect for you, simply because I love you. Love doesn't depend on what you think of yourself. Love doesn't depend on the voices in your head. There's nothing that could ever make me stop loving you, Gemi."
Gemi is silent for a moment
And then she just
Hugs Shale tightly and starts to cry
"I....love you....so much...." She says between sobs
Shale pulls her to her chest and rests her chin on top of Gemi's head, stroking her hair quietly. "I love you too, Gemi. We all do. Don't forget that..."
Gemi's intrusive thoughts were silent for now.
Her hug grew tighter
Shale keeps stroking Gemi's hair, humming a soothing, quiet tune.
After about 12 minutes her breathing was regular and she had stopped crying completely
"We should... probably go back inside..."
*and I should learn how to combat my impulsive thoughts...*
"We can chill out here for a little while, if you want. Just the girlfriends, talking." *And kissing, if you want*, Shale thinks, but keeps it to herself.
"I owe Solus an apology."
"..." Shale has no idea what to say in this situation. "Wait a little bit. I'm enjoying just being alone with you here." She blurts.
Gemi blushes and just...kisses her
//what if shale squishes gemi's cheeks now
((hell yes))
Shale grins and pulls back. "Wait a minute. I have payback to get." She squishes Gemi's cheeks and then kisses her fully.
Gemi kisses back, face red. *She's got me good.*
After the kiss ended, all Gemi could say was "...thank you."
"For what? Stating the facts?"
"For just....everything you've done for me. For being yourself." *I owe her my life.*
"Now, you see, I'd love everyone to thank me for being myself more. *Thank you*." Shale gives her signature grin.
Gemi chuckles. "It's good to spend time with my girlfriends."
Gemi just...hugged Shale in silence. Just living in this moment.
*you're gonna screw up eventually*
Gemi ignored the thought
"It is..." Shale grins.
Gemi was humming "Stay With You" by the Goo Goo Dolls
"Should we go back inside?"
Shale shrugs. "Sure, if you want to."
((Sorry. I was burning toothpicks))
//fadfadsfads
((It is my favorite hobby-))
//Valid
Gemi went inside
Shale followed, hands in her pockets
Polaris stood outside the bakery, back to the wall, waiting. He was ready for Helios to come outside— they needed to talk.
The younger mun walked out, looking for Polaris. Once he spotted him Helio walked over. "You uh....wanted to talk...?"
He turned his head to Helios and nodded, pushing himself off the wall and standing up straight, hands in his pockets. “That thing you told me about earlier. Explain.”

He nodded "The Plasma....they....forced me to throw you into a time loop.....using my stand....It was against my will. I was told if I didnt obey...I would be punished as well.....And...that terrified me...." His wings had wrapped around his body while his tail flicked a bit
“What kind of a time loop?” he asked. He wanted to get straight to the point.
".... A Death Time Loop........." He was nervous..
“...” he smacked his face with his hand. “Fuck..” he mumbled, mostly to himself.
"Im sorry...." He rubbed his arm a bit "I really didnt wanna do it....."
“...hey kid, how old’re ya?”
"Im only....15,000....but in human years i was 15...."

“Then I have no right to be more hurt than you. If someone made me do that at 15...” he grumbled, scowling at the thought of it before shaking his head. “Whatever. Don’t worry about it, I’m not mad at you. Thanks for being honest with me,” he said, walking up to Helio and rubbing his hair a bit.
The smaller mun nodded "Its no problem....you deserve to know the truth....!"
“Mhm. You seem like a good kid— grow up staying good, alright?” he asked, more of a statement than anything.
He nodded "That's...my plan..." Helio chuckled
“Good,” he nodded, patting Helio on the shoulder before heading off.
